In medium saucepan heat 1 tablespoon oil until hot. Add onion and garlic; cook 3 minutes or until onion is tender; stirring occasionally. Add roasted peppers, broth and salt; stir gently to mix. Cover; cook 5 minutes. Transfer roasted pepper mixture to blender container or food processor bowl with metal blade; cover blend until smooth. In medium skillet heat remaining 1 tablespoon olive oil over medium heat until hot. Add shrimp; cook and stir 4 to 5 minutes or until shrimp turn pink. Stir in basil. To serve, place about 1/2 cup sauce on each individual serving plate. Drizzle cream over sauce, top with shrimp. Serve with steamed vegetables if desired.